**Database Schema Design**

We will design a database schema for a Todo List application using a relational database management system (RDBMS) like PostgreSQL. The schema will be normalized to 3NF to minimize data redundancy and improve data integrity.

**Todo List Database Schema**

```sql
-- todo_list.sql

-- Create a new database for the Todo List application
CREATE DATABASE todo_list;

-- Use the todo_list database
\c todo_list

-- Create a table for users
CREATE TABLE users (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    email VARCHAR(255) UNIQUE NOT NULL,
    password_hash VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- Create a table for todo lists
CREATE TABLE todo_lists (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    user_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES users(id),
    title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- Create a table for todo items
CREATE TABLE todo_items (
    id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY,
    todo_list_id INTEGER NOT NULL REFERENCES todo_lists(id),
    title VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL,
    description TEXT,
    due_date DATE,
    completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
    created_at TIMESTAMP NOT NULL DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
);

-- Create an index on the todo_items table for efficient querying
CREATE INDEX idx_todo_items_todo_list_id ON todo_items(todo_list_id);
CREATE INDEX idx_todo_items_completed ON todo_items(completed);
```

